<subSubSection pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="72.[124,653,193,568]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
ETYMOLOGY: The trivial name is taken from the Latin feminine 
<emphasis box="[414,493,516,539]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">sagitta</emphasis>
(arrow). I refer to the arrow­shaped apex of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
